name: Cauliflower
description: Steamed, boiled, saut√©ed or raw, cauliflower is a great addition to any dish.  The distinct white florets allow it to stand out amongst its colourful vegetable companions. It can be found all year long, and is a favourite to eat raw with a dip. It is also a great substitute for rice and Potatoes.

name: Carrots
description: Carrots are integral in adding colour and sweet flavour to soups, stews, salads and stir fries .

name: Celery
description: Whether chopped up in salad, eaten raw with butter or included in your favourite soup, celery is a multi-purpose vegetable. This large vegetable provides a satisfying crunch no matter the occasion and stores well in the refrigerator.

name: Mushrooms, Brown Whole
description: Brown mushrooms can be eaten raw or cooked.            They make a great substitute for white mushrooms.  They are perfect for salads and soups.
